#: ../../source/deployment/deployment.md:144
msgid ""
"For enterprise deployments, the Mattermost database can be configured "
"with a master and multiple read replicas. The read replicas can be "
"configured as a redundant backup to the active server, so that during "
"hardware failures operation can be diverted to the read replica server "
"without interrupting service. The safest configuration is to size the "
"disk space on the read replica used for failover two to three times "
"larger than storage available on master, so that if the master fails "
"because it runs out of disk space it will fail over to a read replica "
"with enough extra space to run smoothly until the master is corrected."
